<article class="c-article c-article--home">
  <div class="l-container--lg">

    <h1 class="c-heading c-heading--lg">Hi, I'm Jesse!</h1>
    <p class="c-subtitle">I care a lot about empowering people with technology.</p>

    <div class="c-article__body">

      <p>I've been doing full-stack web design and development for over 25 years. I specialize in user experience design, technical strategy, system architecture, software development, and improving accessibility at scale with design systems.</p>

      <p>I'm currently the Director of Accessibility and Design Systems for New York State. I lead several teams dedicated to improving the resident experience and accessibility of the state's digital applications at scale with user research, design systems, and responsible AI.</p>

      <p>Our design system team recently launched v1.0 of the <a href="https://designsystem.ny.gov">New York State Design System</a>, and our accessibility team is currently helping engineers remediate the top public-facing workflows for NYS agencies ahead of the DOJ Title II accessibility deadline.</p>

      <p>I've also been exploring the role of generative AI in civic tech, especially in the context of code generation. The Design System we created is a library of design components mapped to a library of accessible, tested code components, which gives AI the context it needs to produce predictable, consistent code. I presented a talk about our approach at <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=formfest2025">FormFest 2025</a> or you can watch a <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/jessegardner_shorter-version">shorter version on LinkedIn</a>. I'm also scheduled to present "Design systems as AI infrastructure" at <a href="https://intodesignsystems.com">Into Design Systems Conference 2026</a>.</p>

      <p>I'm always looking to connect the dots between design and engineering. I've written a lot about ways to bridge that gap over at <a href="https://practicaldesignsystems.com">Practical Design Systems</a>.</p>

      <p>Before NYS, I served as a VP of Technology at Fox, where I migrated several large media sites to a custom content platform, managed several client teams, and helped launch Fox Weather. Before that, I worked at Simply Recipes, designing and helping grow one of the world's most trusted food blogs, and at AMC Networks, unifying multiple content platforms into a single content platform for all of the company's business units. I've also helped clients like Asurion, Boeing, and Harvard with various design and development challenges.</p>

      <hr>

      <p>I currently live in Upstate NY with my wife and four kids. When I'm not solving problems, I tend to my hobby farm, make candles with my wife, snap landscape photos, and promote empathy through storytelling. I also write (infrequently) about technology, politics, and the human condition over on <a href="/blog/">my blog</a>.</p>

    </div>

    {% include "partials/end-mark.njk" %}

  </div>
</article>

